spans.text: of many a daring wight , Who never before in verse essayed to write , Attendant fly , impregnating the air With Ode and Sonnet to the blooming fair , To me , your suppliant , deign to wast a breeze From Avon's banks
So first taking in a great gulp of the air , And trying to find the poetical chair
you my history with speed I prepare
a chameleon , and live on the air , Or like poets of old
Two rooms by the year under fifty good pound
to spend all one's worth , It's best to bestow it on pleasure and mirth , So at Bath will I live
